DTSTART:20160425T223019Z
DTEND:20160425T231059Z
DTSTAMP:20160424T225025Z
DESCRIPTION:With all the storage options in OpenStack\, every user will ne
 ed to move data around\, either within a cloud from one storage type or ba
 ckend to another or from one cloud to another. We are going to discuss mig
 ration approaches for images\, volumes and shares provided by Glance\, Cin
 der and Manila OpenStack services\, and apply this to different backends s
 uch Ceph\, NFS\, iSCSI. Our talk is geared toward end users\, administrato
 rs and architects\, and will cover both in-cloud and multi-cloud migration
 \, which is especially important in the context of an inevitable cloud upg
 rade.Use cases include cloud migration\, storage scaling and disaster reco
 very will illustrate tools and techniques appropriate for each.We are team
 ing up to tender tales\, tools and techniques to technical teams in order 
 to transfer troves of terabytes to tenable targets.
