BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cinder and Docker\, Like Peanut Butter and Chocolate
DTSTART:20160426T161519Z
DTEND:20160426T165559Z
DTSTAMP:20160424T225025Z
DESCRIPTION:Cinder has seen explosive growth offering over 70 backend stor
 age providers.  Now we're seeing the arms race begin with Vendors and sta
 rt-ups pitching the same sort of trend in Containers.  Did you know howev
 er that it's actually pretty simple to use Cinder to provide your Block St
 orage orchestration for Docker?  Many point out that Containers and OpenS
 tack can be complimentary\, we'll show you one such case. This talk will 
 introduce some of the current functionality in the Docker Volumes API as w
 ell as take a quick look at a number of the options that are out there.  
 There's no single answer\, but there might be an easier path to Persistent
  Block storage in containers than you thought.  We'll show you how you ca
 n use your existing Cinder environment an introduce a Native Docker Cinder
  plugin\, and how some folks are already using this great combination toda
 y!  Not to mention a demo with the potential for spectacular failure that
  you can tweet about and tell all your friends!  
LOCATION:Austin Convention Center - Level 4 - Ballroom E
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Freezer: From Backup/Restore aaS to a Fully DR Solution for OpenSt
 ack
DTSTART:20160426T170500Z
DTEND:20160426T174540Z
DTSTAMP:20160424T225025Z
